"Axial Stiffness Matrix — From Shape Functions to K
'K = ∫ Bᵀ·E·A·B dx (Logan Ch.3)

"Shape Functions
#deq N_1 = 1 - ξ
#deq N_2 = ξ

"B Matrix (derivative of N)
#sym diff(1-t; t)
#sym diff(t; t)
#deq B = [-1/L; 1/L]

"Stiffness Matrix
#deq K = B^T*E*A*B*L = E*A/L*[1; -1 | -1; 1]

"Numerical Example
E = 200000MPa
A = 100cm^2
L = 3m
K = E*A/L*[1; -1 | -1; 1]
K|[kN/m; kN/m | kN/m; kN/m]

"Solve: Fixed at node 1, F=100kN at node 2
F = 100kN
u_2 = F/(E*A/L)
u_2|mm
